Common Test Steps (Used as Base)

Use this as the starting point for every Mitigation Plan test case.

1. Login to Service Bench application.
2. Navigate to Conduct Risk Assessment plugins → Click Conduct Risk Assessment plugin → Click on Initiate Risk Assessment.
3. Select Project ID and impacted Business Functions with RFO.
4. Click on Submit.
5. Complete Risk Assessment Part 1.
6. Complete Risk Assessment Part 2.
7. Click Next to navigate to Mitigation Plan / Commentary stage.

⸻

1. Verify Header

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Observe the page header.

Expected Result

1. User is navigated to Mitigation Plan / Commentary stage.
2. Header is displayed as Conduct - Risk Assessment.
3. Mitigation Plan / Commentary stage is highlighted.

⸻

2. Verify Details Panel

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Observe the Details panel.

Expected Result

1. Details panel is displayed.
2. Case ID, Initiative ID, Programme ID, Initiative Name, Programme Name and Impacted Business Function are displayed.
3. Details are read-only.

⸻

3. Verify Warning Message

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Observe the warning banner.

Expected Result

1. Sensitive Data Warning is displayed.

⸻

4. Verify Guidelines

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Observe the Guidelines section.
9. Click View Guideline.

Expected Result

1. Guidelines section is displayed.
2. Guideline document opens successfully.

⸻

5. Verify Conduct Risks are displayed

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Observe the mitigation grid.

Expected Result

1. All Conduct Risk Areas from Part 2 are displayed.
2. Conduct Risk Description and Impact Scale are displayed.

⸻

6. Verify Search

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Enter Conduct Risk Area name in Search box.
9. Press Enter/Search.

Expected Result

1. Matching Conduct Risk Areas are displayed.

⸻

7. Verify Add Mitigation Plan popup

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.

Expected Result

1. Add/Edit Mitigation Plan popup opens.

⸻

8. Verify Conduct Risk Area dropdown

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Click Conduct Risk Area dropdown.

Expected Result

1. Only eligible Conduct Risk Areas are displayed.
2. User can select one Conduct Risk Area.

⸻

9. Verify Impact Scale display

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Select a Conduct Risk Area.

Expected Result

1. Corresponding Impact Scale is displayed.
2. Impact Scale is read-only.

⸻

10. Verify Conduct Risk Description

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Select a Conduct Risk Area.

Expected Result

1. Conduct Risk Description from Part 2 is displayed.
2. Description is read-only.

⸻

11. Verify Mitigation Plan mandatory for Red

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Select a Red Conduct Risk Area.
10. Leave Mitigation Plan blank.
11. Select Conduct Outcome.
12. Click Submit.

Expected Result

1. Validation message is displayed.
2. Record is not saved.

⸻

12. Verify Mitigation Plan mandatory for Amber

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Select an Amber Conduct Risk Area.
10. Leave Mitigation Plan blank.
11. Select Conduct Outcome.
12. Click Submit.

Expected Result

1. Validation message is displayed.
2. Record is not saved.

⸻

13. Verify Green Commentary

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Select a Green Conduct Risk Area.

Expected Result

1. Commentary field is displayed.
2. Mitigation fields applicable to Red/Amber are not displayed.

⸻

14. Verify 5000 Character Limit

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Enter more than 5000 characters in Mitigation Plan/Commentary.

Expected Result

1. Maximum 5000 characters are allowed.
2. Character counter is displayed correctly.

⸻

15. Verify Conduct Outcome dropdown

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Click Conduct Outcome dropdown.

Expected Result

1. All available Conduct Outcomes are displayed.

⸻

16. Verify maximum two Conduct Outcomes

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Select first Conduct Outcome.
10. Select second Conduct Outcome.
11. Attempt to select third Conduct Outcome.

Expected Result

1. Only two Conduct Outcomes can be selected.
2. Third selection is prevented.

⸻

17. Verify Conduct Outcome mandatory

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Enter Mitigation Plan.
10. Leave Conduct Outcome blank.
11. Click Submit.

Expected Result

1. Validation message is displayed.
2. Record is not saved.

⸻

18. Verify Upload document

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Upload a supported document.
10. Click Submit.

Expected Result

1. Document uploads successfully.
2. Uploaded document is displayed.

⸻

19. Verify Submit Mitigation Plan

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Select Conduct Risk Area.
10. Enter Mitigation Plan/Commentary.
11. Select Conduct Outcomes.
12. Upload document if required.
13. Click Submit.

Expected Result

1. Mitigation Plan is saved.
2. Record is displayed in the mitigation grid.

⸻

20. Verify Cancel

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Enter Mitigation details.
10. Click Cancel.

Expected Result

1. Popup closes.
2. Changes are discarded.

⸻

21. Verify Edit

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Add and save a Mitigation Plan.
9. Click Action menu.
10. Click Edit.
11. Modify Mitigation Plan.
12. Click Submit.

Expected Result

1. Changes are saved.
2. Updated details are displayed in the grid.

⸻

22. Verify Delete

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Add and save a Mitigation Plan.
9. Click Action menu.
10. Click Delete.
11. Confirm deletion.

Expected Result

1. Selected Mitigation Plan is deleted.
2. Record is removed from the grid.

⸻

23. Verify Audit Log

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Add and save a Mitigation Plan.
9. Click Action menu.
10. Click Audit Log.

Expected Result

1. Audit history is displayed for the selected Conduct Risk Area.

⸻

24. Verify Previous

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Previous.

Expected Result

1. User is navigated back to Risk Assessment Part 2.

⸻

25. Verify Next

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Complete all mandatory Mitigation Plans.
9. Click Next.

Expected Result

1. User is navigated to RFO Comments stage.

⸻

26. Verify Save as Draft

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Enter Mitigation details.
9. Click Save as Draft.
10. Reopen the assessment.

Expected Result

1. Assessment is saved as Draft.
2. Previously entered details are retained.

⸻

27. Verify Clear All

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Enter Mitigation details.
9. Click Clear All.
10. Confirm the action.

Expected Result

1. All unsaved Mitigation Plan details are cleared.
2. Screen is reset.

⸻

28. Verify Submit Assessment

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Complete all mandatory Mitigation Plans.
9. Click Submit.

Expected Result

1. Assessment is submitted successfully.
2. Success message is displayed.

⸻

29. Verify completed Conduct Risk Areas are not available in Add dropdown

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Add and save a Mitigation Plan for one Conduct Risk Area.
9. Click Add.
10. Open Conduct Risk Area dropdown.

Expected Result

1. Previously completed Conduct Risk Area is not displayed.
2. Only pending Conduct Risk Areas are available.

⸻

30. Verify Green popup displays only Green fields

Test Steps

1-7 Common Test Steps.
8. Click Add.
9. Select a Green Conduct Risk Area.

Expected Result

1. Conduct Risk Area, Impact Scale and Description are displayed.
2. Commentary field is displayed.
3. Conduct Outcome dropdown is displayed.
4. Fields applicable only to Red/Amber are not displayed
